Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.32,0:00:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,,We look forward to
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.75,0:00:06.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Anthony Morris’ thoughts
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.82,0:00:09.86,Default,,0,0,0,,presented in his talk entitled
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.86,0:00:12.46,Default,,0,0,0,,“We Have Work to Do!”
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.56,0:00:18.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a great pleasure\Nto hear all of the excitement
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.17,0:00:22.97,Default,,0,0,0,,when the Ramapo project\Nwas announced to all of you here,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.97,0:00:27.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and I’m sure that was true\Nfor the other thousands that are tied in.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.98,0:00:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you saw with these videos
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.48,0:00:32.52,Default,,0,0,0,,all the construction projects
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.52,0:00:36.02,Default,,0,0,0,,going on all over\N—all over the earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.02,0:00:38.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So it’s quite interesting,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.15,0:00:42.76,Default,,0,0,0,,if you think about it\Nfrom an imperfect, human perspective
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.76,0:00:45.66,Default,,0,0,0,,(frankly, not thinking spiritually),
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.66,0:00:50.67,Default,,0,0,0,,you’d say:\N“Well, we just dedicated the Warwick property
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.67,0:00:54.07,Default,,0,0,0,,“along with Wallkill recently.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.07,0:00:59.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Now here we go down the road.”
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.81,0:01:05.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the preaching work\Nobviously is premier.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.82,0:01:09.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And that’s what this is really about\N—the preaching work.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.39,0:01:11.79,Default,,0,0,0,,To support the preaching work
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.79,0:01:15.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and to continue to feed\NJehovah’s precious sheep
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.06,0:01:19.97,Default,,0,0,0,,the way he wants them fed\Ninvolves all this construction.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.96,0:01:24.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So God wants us to have it clear.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.47,0:01:28.57,Default,,0,0,0,,He wants you to spread this and,\Nof course, it’ll come up in January.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.57,0:01:32.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep in mind, we have work to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.01,0:01:33.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Period.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.34,0:01:34.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So get over it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.65,0:01:41.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t get me going on vacation.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.65,0:01:42.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ll just tell you—
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.79,0:01:45.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And I know my friends on the Governing Body,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.59,0:01:48.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and I know that you need your time.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.26,0:01:52.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m not trying to put you on a guilt trip,\Nbut we have a whole lot of days.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.00,0:01:57.50,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you do it\Nwith the work that’s going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.50,0:02:00.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You try to rest up when you can;\NJehovah wants us to.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.74,0:02:03.21,Default,,0,0,0,,But we have so much work to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.21,0:02:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And we thank God for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.87,0:02:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So just to give us\Na little Scriptural reminder
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.24,0:02:11.38,Default,,0,0,0,,of the proper attitude about work,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.38,0:02:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,find John chapter 5.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.48,0:02:16.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And these are\Nvery familiar verses to all of you,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.85,0:02:19.45,Default,,0,0,0,,particularly the audience here in Newburgh
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.46,0:02:23.06,Default,,0,0,0,,with all these decades of faithful service.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.06,0:02:26.73,Default,,0,0,0,,We treasure your service
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.73,0:02:29.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and, of course,\NJehovah certainly does.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.50,0:02:31.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And you’ve worked hard for decades
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.53,0:02:34.03,Default,,0,0,0,,—a lot of you to whom\NI was talking to earlier
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.04,0:02:36.04,Default,,0,0,0,,have decades in the traveling work—
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.04,0:02:39.28,Default,,0,0,0,,so many wonderful,\Nhardworking brothers and sisters.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.28,0:02:42.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So here he is, Jesus, (in John chapter 5)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.25,0:02:47.06,Default,,0,0,0,,facing these judgmental religious leaders
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.05,0:02:50.55,Default,,0,0,0,,persecuting him over curing on the Sabbath.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.55,0:02:55.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, what we’re after here\Nis something he reveals to us in verse 17,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.56,0:02:58.76,Default,,0,0,0,,when he’s answering them:
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.76,0:03:02.60,Default,,0,0,0,,“My Father has kept working until now,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.60,0:03:05.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and I keep working.”
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.10,0:03:07.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So the hardest worker\Nin the universe is Jehovah God,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.94,0:03:10.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and Christ Jesus is right there with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.77,0:03:13.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah is a worker.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.11,0:03:15.85,Default,,0,0,0,,His people have to be workers.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.85,0:03:19.29,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s what he expects,\Nand it’s such a pleasure
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.28,0:03:22.72,Default,,0,0,0,,to serve the true God and work.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.72,0:03:26.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And another familiar verse\Nin 1 Corinthians chapter 15
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.89,0:03:30.76,Default,,0,0,0,,shows the proper spirit\Nwhen it comes to this matter
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.76,0:03:34.16,Default,,0,0,0,,of being workers,\Nwith all the work we have to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.16,0:03:38.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And Jehovah is seeing to it\Nthat we have all this work
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.87,0:03:43.74,Default,,0,0,0,,—very familiar,\Nverse 58 of 1 Corinthians 15:
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.74,0:03:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,“Therefore, my beloved brothers,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.88,0:03:49.18,Default,,0,0,0,,“be steadfast, immovable,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.18,0:03:52.62,Default,,0,0,0,,“[notice] {\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}always {\r} having plenty to do
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.62,0:03:55.52,Default,,0,0,0,,“in the work of the Lord,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.52,0:03:58.92,Default,,0,0,0,,knowing that your labor\Nis not in vain in connection with the Lord”
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.92,0:04:03.82,Default,,0,0,0,,—plenty of work “in the work of the Lord.”
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.83,0:04:05.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And then when we’re doing the work
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.83,0:04:08.77,Default,,0,0,0,,(and this is crucial),\Nas we engage in it
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.77,0:04:12.07,Default,,0,0,0,,—whether it’s the preaching work\Nor other work assignments,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.07,0:04:15.84,Default,,0,0,0,,if you’re in a Bethel assignment\Nor a construction assignment—
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.84,0:04:17.94,Default,,0,0,0,,there’s a proper spirit.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.94,0:04:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And find here Romans chapter 12.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.28,0:04:24.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And this we see in God’s people,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.18,0:04:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,but we want to individually apply the counsel
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.92,0:04:30.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and make sure we keep this spirit
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.19,0:04:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,or talk to God about it\Nif it’s lacking at the moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.52,0:04:36.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Romans chapter 12
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.93,0:04:40.63,Default,,0,0,0,,—and here’s what Christians are all about
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.63,0:04:43.03,Default,,0,0,0,,when it comes to working for Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.03,0:04:48.04,Default,,0,0,0,,verse 11:\N“Be industrious, not lazy.”
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.04,0:04:52.38,Default,,0,0,0,,See, Jehovah does not approve of being lazy.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.94,0:04:56.21,Default,,0,0,0,,“Be aglow with the spirit.”
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.21,0:04:57.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So you’re just absorbed with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.88,0:05:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,There’s this zeal\N—just alive with it—
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.48,0:05:04.08,Default,,0,0,0,,as we slave for Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.09,0:05:06.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So he appreciates
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.26,0:05:10.47,Default,,0,0,0,,an industrious, hardworking spirit,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.46,0:05:13.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and that’s what he wants from his people.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.50,0:05:16.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, with all of the announcements
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.77,0:05:19.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and the videos\Nwith construction going on,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.07,0:05:21.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I just thought I’d share this with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.30,0:05:24.87,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s a very special item of mine,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.87,0:05:29.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and it came up recently.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.01,0:05:31.31,Default,,0,0,0,,You can see here the best you can.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.31,0:05:33.31,Default,,0,0,0,,The camera can pick it up,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.32,0:05:36.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and up here it says “Building Permit.”
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.79,0:05:39.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And it’s a special memory for me, personally,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.86,0:05:42.53,Default,,0,0,0,,because as we had in some of the videos
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.53,0:05:45.77,Default,,0,0,0,,when we were involved with the construction
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.76,0:05:50.23,Default,,0,0,0,,or before construction started\Nwith the Warwick project,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.23,0:05:54.77,Default,,0,0,0,,we’d be at Tuxedo,\Nand a lot of work was going on
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.77,0:05:58.21,Default,,0,0,0,,—preparatory—\Nlooking for that day
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.21,0:06:00.51,Default,,0,0,0,,when they could get started.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.51,0:06:03.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So the Governing Body\Nwould do their best to get up
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.68,0:06:08.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and be encouraging\N(always wearing the high-vis outfits)
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.08,0:06:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and then give a spiritual talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.89,0:06:14.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it’s the only time\NI’ve given a talk in high vis.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.93,0:06:19.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So this particular day was special
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.46,0:06:22.73,Default,,0,0,0,,because things\Nwere moving along with the community.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.73,0:06:27.13,Default,,0,0,0,,They liked us,\Nbut I noticed Zeny (in the one video),
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.14,0:06:29.18,Default,,0,0,0,,he mentioned “shovel to the ground,”
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.17,0:06:30.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and that’s OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.17,0:06:31.17,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re different.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.17,0:06:34.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m calling it “shovel in the ground.”
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.38,0:06:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Zeny is not from America,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.28,0:06:41.12,Default,,0,0,0,,so it means the same thing, Zeny,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.12,0:06:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,so forgive me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.92,0:06:46.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I appreciate all your hard work.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.42,0:06:50.16,Default,,0,0,0,,But any who\Nhave been involved with construction
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.16,0:06:54.83,Default,,0,0,0,,(and you have a lot of folks I know here\Nfrom the former Regional Building Committee
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.83,0:06:57.83,Default,,0,0,0,,—all the hardworking construction),
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.83,0:07:02.23,Default,,0,0,0,,it’s always been special\Nto work on these spiritual projects.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.24,0:07:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, this particular day,\Nthere were a lot of things going on.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.24,0:07:09.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So I’m up there; it’s July 26,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.65,0:07:13.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and that date is up here in the corner.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.08,0:07:15.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s a Friday,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.22,0:07:19.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and it’s the year 2013 (quite a while ago).
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.52,0:07:24.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So I have a talk to give to them\Nat 1:30 p.m. after visiting some.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.46,0:07:27.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Two hours before
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.13,0:07:31.33,Default,,0,0,0,,(so it must have been around 11:30),
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.33,0:07:34.17,Default,,0,0,0,,they got the building permit.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.17,0:07:37.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So the Construction Project Committee
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.97,0:07:41.47,Default,,0,0,0,,(and how much we love \Nthose men and their wives)—
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.48,0:07:43.85,Default,,0,0,0,,They’re there, and they said,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.85,0:07:46.49,Default,,0,0,0,,“Well, would you mind\Nmaking this announcement?”
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.48,0:07:49.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And I thought:\N‘Boy, that timing worked out good.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.05,0:07:52.79,Default,,0,0,0,,‘That’s quite an honor,\Nthe construction, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.79,0:07:55.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and “the shovel-in-the-ground” announcement.’
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.79,0:07:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So I gave them a little spiritual side.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.96,0:08:03.37,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, a little glory is all right\Nfor a human sometimes, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.60,0:08:07.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So it was very exciting.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.97,0:08:10.94,Default,,0,0,0,,But the memory is clear\Nto those who were there.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.94,0:08:14.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of the operation of holy spirit
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.24,0:08:18.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and the brothers\Nbeing “aglow with the spirit,” industrious,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.41,0:08:21.31,Default,,0,0,0,,when they made the announcement,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.32,0:08:24.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m telling you (those who were there),
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.05,0:08:28.19,Default,,0,0,0,,there was joy\N—the thunderous applause.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.19,0:08:30.29,Default,,0,0,0,,It wasn’t anything to do with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.29,0:08:32.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It was that they got\N“the shovel in the ground.”
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.83,0:08:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And the excitement!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.00,0:08:38.87,Default,,0,0,0,,So I was able to easily walk out of there,\Nand they were all busy
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.87,0:08:43.88,Default,,0,0,0,,—thrilled\Nover the “shovel-in-the-ground” approval.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.87,0:08:48.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the day is coming, God willing,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.24,0:08:52.95,Default,,0,0,0,,for the Ramapo project\Nto have the “shovel in the ground.”
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.95,0:08:55.45,Default,,0,0,0,,You heard when they hope that happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.45,0:08:59.82,Default,,0,0,0,,But it’s that beautiful spirit\Nthat glorifies Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.82,0:09:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,when they work so hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.86,0:09:04.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we have to keep that spirit.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.69,0:09:07.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And some could say
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.06,0:09:09.10,Default,,0,0,0,,(well, it happens on occasion,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.10,0:09:13.81,Default,,0,0,0,,not with a lot\Nof God’s spiritually-minded folks):
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.80,0:09:15.97,Default,,0,0,0,,“Do you believe the end is coming?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.97,0:09:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,“So, what are you doing all this for?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.24,0:09:21.24,Default,,0,0,0,,“If the end is really close,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.24,0:09:23.34,Default,,0,0,0,,what are you doing?”
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.35,0:09:25.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the end is going to come
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.62,0:09:28.12,Default,,0,0,0,,when Jehovah is satisfied\Nwith the preaching work.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.12,0:09:32.42,Default,,0,0,0,,But there is also a reminder here\Nin Revelation chapter 7;
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.42,0:09:36.16,Default,,0,0,0,,this is always something you can forget.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.16,0:09:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I noticed Brother Butler
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.79,0:09:41.59,Default,,0,0,0,,touched on it in his opening prayer
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.60,0:09:44.60,Default,,0,0,0,,(which, of course, we don’t record
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.60,0:09:47.14,Default,,0,0,0,,the prayers for the presentation in January),
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.14,0:09:50.28,Default,,0,0,0,,but Bob touched on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.27,0:09:53.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And Jehovah gives us\Nenough to keep us focused on:
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.74,0:09:56.38,Default,,0,0,0,,‘You just stay busy and do my will.’
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.38,0:09:59.55,Default,,0,0,0,,However, this is quite fascinating
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.55,0:10:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,at chapter 7 verses 1-3:
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.49,0:10:08.83,Default,,0,0,0,,“After this I saw four angels standing\Non the four corners of the earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.82,0:10:10.82,Default,,0,0,0,,“holding tight the four winds of the earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.83,0:10:13.37,Default,,0,0,0,,“so that no wind could blow on the earth
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.36,0:10:16.66,Default,,0,0,0,,“or on the sea or on any tree.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.67,0:10:19.51,Default,,0,0,0,,“And I saw another angel\Nascending from the sunrise,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.50,0:10:21.80,Default,,0,0,0,,“having a seal of the living God;
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.80,0:10:25.27,Default,,0,0,0,,“and he called\Nwith a loud voice to the four angels
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.27,0:10:28.51,Default,,0,0,0,,“to whom it was granted\Nto harm the earth and the sea,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.51,0:10:30.51,Default,,0,0,0,,“saying: [and it’s loud]
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.51,0:10:34.65,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Do not harm the earth\Nor the sea or the trees,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.65,0:10:38.09,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘until after we have sealed
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.09,0:10:41.86,Default,,0,0,0,,the slaves of our God in their foreheads.’”
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.93,0:10:48.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, some individual anointed\Nhave to have a final seal
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.66,0:10:50.70,Default,,0,0,0,,before they die,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.70,0:10:54.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and we’ve had a number of them\Ndie during the last days.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.44,0:10:58.51,Default,,0,0,0,,But this is talking\Nabout right before Jehovah starts,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.51,0:11:02.18,Default,,0,0,0,,or has put it in the hearts\Nof the governments to destroy Babylon,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.18,0:11:04.85,Default,,0,0,0,,that all of those who are left on the earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.85,0:11:08.65,Default,,0,0,0,,the remnant\N—genuine, anointed disciples of Christ—
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.65,0:11:11.12,Default,,0,0,0,,get the final seal.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.12,0:11:13.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is what’s going to take place.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.66,0:11:18.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And then after that,\Nthe great tribulation breaks out.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.23,0:11:22.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you keep an eye\Non the news to some degree
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.03,0:11:26.20,Default,,0,0,0,,(if you can stomach it,\Nto at least know what’s happening),
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.20,0:11:28.90,Default,,0,0,0,,the end is definitely close.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.90,0:11:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,There’s just no denying it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.01,0:11:34.65,Default,,0,0,0,,We eagerly look forward to it taking place.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.64,0:11:38.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The great tribulation\N—it’s close.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.08,0:11:41.25,Default,,0,0,0,,However, as we eagerly await it,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.25,0:11:45.45,Default,,0,0,0,,we want to have Jehovah’s mind\Non the matter and wait patiently.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.45,0:11:47.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And I think about all of those
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.79,0:11:50.99,Default,,0,0,0,,here in Newburgh
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.99,0:11:53.16,Default,,0,0,0,,with so many years in the truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.16,0:11:57.06,Default,,0,0,0,,especially corporate members\Nand their mates (if they’re married).
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.07,0:12:01.67,Default,,0,0,0,,This {\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}Watchtower,{\r}\Nwe want to share it with you from 1976
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.67,0:12:04.97,Default,,0,0,0,,—profound statements.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.97,0:12:09.61,Default,,0,0,0,,To this day, they ring true\Nabout this matter of the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.61,0:12:13.41,Default,,0,0,0,,It shows you where\Nwe are in the stream of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.42,0:12:15.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And Jehovah’s spirit was on them
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.42,0:12:19.06,Default,,0,0,0,,(not inspired,\Nbut he captured it with them, helping them),
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.05,0:12:23.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and it was just ringing,\Nand it still rings to this day.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.03,0:12:27.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Now notice what\Nthat 1976, November 15, {\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}Watchtower {\r} said,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.96,0:12:31.33,Default,,0,0,0,,pages 688-689.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.33,0:12:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And in the 17th paragraph,\Nnotice, I’m quoting it:
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.40,0:12:36.40,Default,,0,0,0,,“The end does not come
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.41,0:12:39.51,Default,,0,0,0,,“just because we might think\Nit is the due date,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.51,0:12:44.15,Default,,0,0,0,,“or because we feel that our territory\Nhas been well worked.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.15,0:12:46.72,Default,,0,0,0,,“It comes when Jehovah has carried through
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.72,0:12:51.73,Default,,0,0,0,,“the great work of Kingdom preaching\Nto the extent he wants,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.72,0:12:55.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and then he will bring\Nthe ‘great tribulation.’”
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.56,0:12:58.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Now listen, back in 1976:
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.43,0:13:02.43,Default,,0,0,0,,“Until that time there is work to do!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.13,0:13:08.30,Default,,0,0,0,,“And we as Jehovah’s Witnesses\Nare the ones assigned to do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.71,0:13:11.88,Default,,0,0,0,,“The arrival of the ‘great tribulation’
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.87,0:13:16.37,Default,,0,0,0,,“should find the preaching work\Nat the height of its forward movement,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.38,0:13:21.39,Default,,0,0,0,,“at the very peak\Nof its momentum throughout the earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.38,0:13:23.82,Default,,0,0,0,,“The arrival of the Lord Jesus
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.82,0:13:27.59,Default,,0,0,0,,“to execute judgment\Nwill come as a complete surprise
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.59,0:13:30.69,Default,,0,0,0,,“—even to Jehovah’s people,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.69,0:13:34.23,Default,,0,0,0,,“for it will no doubt find them
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.23,0:13:37.63,Default,,0,0,0,,at their busiest time of activity!”
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.10,0:13:41.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Think about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.10,0:13:45.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you been busier\Nsince you’ve been in the truth
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.14,0:13:47.84,Default,,0,0,0,,than you’ve been recently?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.84,0:13:52.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So we’re the busiest we’ve been
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.52,0:13:55.49,Default,,0,0,0,,—hands down.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.48,0:13:57.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So it’s amazing how the slave
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.72,0:14:01.26,Default,,0,0,0,,captured that right attitude in 1976.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.26,0:14:04.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And, of course, some in the truth then,\Nat least in certain parts of the earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.53,0:14:07.83,Default,,0,0,0,,they were thinking the end is coming in 1975.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.83,0:14:10.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And look at all the growth since the 1970’s.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.07,0:14:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You had about two million back in the 1970’s
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.84,0:14:15.94,Default,,0,0,0,,who were Witnesses of the true God.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.94,0:14:18.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we’re approaching nine million.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.24,0:14:23.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So in conclusion, as closing thoughts,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.38,0:14:26.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and this is priceless\Nfrom that same {\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}Watchtower:
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.02,0:14:29.02,Default,,0,0,0,,“Jehovah’s advancing theocratic society
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.02,0:14:33.99,Default,,0,0,0,,“will be a going concern,\Na go-forward organization,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.99,0:14:38.33,Default,,0,0,0,,right down to\Nand through the ‘great tribulation.’”
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.33,0:14:41.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So like I’ve told brothers for a long time,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.46,0:14:44.56,Default,,0,0,0,,the recent changes from RBC to now—
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.57,0:14:47.67,Default,,0,0,0,,This is all new world construction\Ngoing on here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.67,0:14:49.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You’re taking this over.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.74,0:14:52.54,Default,,0,0,0,,After Armageddon,\Nyou’re going to just keep on working,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.54,0:14:54.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and others will be trained.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.54,0:14:56.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And then further:
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.61,0:14:59.41,Default,,0,0,0,,“The worship of God,”\N{\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}The Watchtower{\r}{\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif} {\r}{\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif} {\r}said,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.42,0:15:02.86,Default,,0,0,0,,“with spirit and truth is positive,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.85,0:15:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,enthusiastic, spirited and progressive.”
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.52,0:15:09.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And then this is profound:
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.53,0:15:11.73,Default,,0,0,0,,“More and more sections of the earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.73,0:15:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,“in Western lands,\Nin the Orient and elsewhere,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.40,0:15:16.67,Default,,0,0,0,,“are now receiving a thorough witness,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.67,0:15:20.64,Default,,0,0,0,,“and who knows how much farther\Nthe ‘glorious good news’
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.64,0:15:22.98,Default,,0,0,0,,will be sounded . . . before the end!”
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.97,0:15:24.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, God knows.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.81,0:15:27.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And look at the sound of the good news
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.28,0:15:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,being all over the earth
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.28,0:15:32.02,Default,,0,0,0,,—‘the most distant parts of the earth.’
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.01,0:15:35.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So may all of us beg Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.05,0:15:37.79,Default,,0,0,0,,to continue to empower us
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.79,0:15:41.56,Default,,0,0,0,,to keep worshipping him\N“with spirit and truth”
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.56,0:15:43.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and enthusiasm and zeal
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.89,0:15:47.06,Default,,0,0,0,,because we have work to do!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.37,0:15:57.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Brother Morris.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.44,0:16:01.18,Default,,0,0,0,,In the words of 1 Chronicles 28:10,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.18,0:16:05.65,Default,,0,0,0,,we will “be courageous and go to work.”
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.65,0:16:07.79,Default,,0,0,0,,At this time, we ask the question,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.78,0:16:10.15,Default,,0,0,0,,“What Do We Have to Fear?”
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.15,0:16:14.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Mark Sanderson\Nwill address that question now for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.43,0:16:20.43,Default,,0,0,0,,At Revelation 12:17,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.43,0:16:24.83,Default,,0,0,0,,the Bible makes clear\Nthat all of God’s people,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.83,0:16:28.53,Default,,0,0,0,,every one of you here in this room
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.54,0:16:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and every servant of God around this earth
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.97,0:16:35.47,Default,,0,0,0,,who support Jehovah’s anointed ones,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.48,0:16:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,are in a war.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.55,0:16:40.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Now read this thought with me
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.55,0:16:44.29,Default,,0,0,0,,at Revelation 12:17.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.29,0:16:46.29,Default,,0,0,0,,It says:
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.29,0:16:50.86,Default,,0,0,0,,“So the dragon\Nbecame enraged at the woman
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.86,0:16:55.90,Default,,0,0,0,,“and went off to wage war\Nwith the remaining ones of her offspring,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.90,0:16:58.67,Default,,0,0,0,,“who observe the commandments of God
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.67,0:17:01.94,Default,,0,0,0,,“and have the work of bearing witness
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.94,0:17:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,concerning Jesus.”
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.87,0:17:06.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, what does it mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.91,0:17:09.48,Default,,0,0,0,,As our dear Brother Morris would say:
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.48,0:17:12.65,Default,,0,0,0,,“Cheer up!\NThings are only going to get worse.”
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.82,0:17:19.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, if we are in this spiritual war,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.99,0:17:22.63,Default,,0,0,0,,what do we expect?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.62,0:17:24.66,Default,,0,0,0,,With every war
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.66,0:17:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,comes intense, intense hatred.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.60,0:17:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Not surprisingly,\NJesus made it clear
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.63,0:17:36.20,Default,,0,0,0,,that his servants\Nwould not just be disliked,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.21,0:17:38.51,Default,,0,0,0,,but what did Jesus say?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.51,0:17:43.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s read it together at Matthew 24:9
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.71,0:17:50.28,Default,,0,0,0,,—Matthew 24:9.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.29,0:17:52.29,Default,,0,0,0,,He said:
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.29,0:17:55.93,Default,,0,0,0,,“Then people\Nwill hand you over to tribulation
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.92,0:17:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,“and will kill you,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.73,0:18:03.74,Default,,0,0,0,,“and you will be hated by all the nations
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.73,0:18:05.73,Default,,0,0,0,,on account of my name.”
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.07,0:18:09.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So, brothers, what do we expect?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.67,0:18:14.14,Default,,0,0,0,,We expect the hatred of all,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.14,0:18:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,as Jesus said, “all the nations”
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.88,0:18:20.95,Default,,0,0,0,,—not just Eritrea, not just Russia,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.95,0:18:23.55,Default,,0,0,0,,but “all the nations.”
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.55,0:18:28.22,Default,,0,0,0,,But there is something else\Nthat we also must expect in a war.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.22,0:18:30.82,Default,,0,0,0,,There is a very famous quote that says,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.83,0:18:35.84,Default,,0,0,0,,“In war, the first casualty is truth.”
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.83,0:18:40.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And that is exactly what Jesus warned\Nwould happen to God’s people.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.70,0:18:42.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s read it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.04,0:18:45.44,Default,,0,0,0,,In Matthew chapter 5,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.44,0:18:50.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Matthew 5:11, he said:
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.25,0:18:55.02,Default,,0,0,0,,“Happy are you when people\Nreproach you and persecute you
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.02,0:18:57.16,Default,,0,0,0,,“[and then notice this]
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.15,0:19:02.16,Default,,0,0,0,,“and lyingly say every sort of wicked thing
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.16,0:19:05.06,Default,,0,0,0,,against you for my sake.”
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.60,0:19:09.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Brothers, what’s the point?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.13,0:19:12.17,Default,,0,0,0,,We are in a war.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.47,0:19:18.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And we expect\Nto “be hated by all the nations.”
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.37,0:19:21.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And we expect that people
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.78,0:19:26.38,Default,,0,0,0,,will “say every sort of wicked thing”
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.38,0:19:28.52,Default,,0,0,0,,against us.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.52,0:19:30.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, with that in mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.52,0:19:33.86,Default,,0,0,0,,it’s good for us to ask this question:
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.86,0:19:37.60,Default,,0,0,0,,What do we have to fear?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.59,0:19:41.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Well-known statesman Franklin Roosevelt said,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.20,0:19:46.21,Default,,0,0,0,,“The only thing\Nthat we have to fear is fear itself.”
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.20,0:19:48.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, he’s not completely correct,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.90,0:19:52.64,Default,,0,0,0,,but there’s certainly\Na note of truth in what he said.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.64,0:19:55.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, fear is a powerful weapon
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.18,0:19:59.35,Default,,0,0,0,,in the hand\Nof our great adversary, Satan the Devil.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.35,0:20:03.35,Default,,0,0,0,,He will use that weapon against us.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.35,0:20:06.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And what is the danger?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.05,0:20:11.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, brothers,\Nwhen we are afraid, or we are terrified,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.06,0:20:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,we can then be controlled by our enemies.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.06,0:20:18.63,Default,,0,0,0,,The apostle Paul made this very clear
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.63,0:20:21.03,Default,,0,0,0,,in what he said here\Nin Hebrews the second chapter.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.04,0:20:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Will you read this with me, please?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.87,0:20:26.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s look in Hebrews chapter 2;
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.81,0:20:29.51,Default,,0,0,0,,let’s look in verse 14.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.51,0:20:32.38,Default,,0,0,0,,He says:\N“Therefore, since the ‘young children’
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.38,0:20:35.05,Default,,0,0,0,,“are sharers of blood and flesh,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.05,0:20:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,“he also similarly shared in the same things,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.55,0:20:40.65,Default,,0,0,0,,“so that through his death
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.66,0:20:43.70,Default,,0,0,0,,“[now notice this, through his death]
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.69,0:20:45.69,Default,,0,0,0,,“he might bring to nothing
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.69,0:20:48.66,Default,,0,0,0,,“the one having\Nthe means to cause death, 
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.66,0:20:50.70,Default,,0,0,0,,“that is, the Devil,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.70,0:20:54.77,Default,,0,0,0,,“and that he might\N[do what? that he might]
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.77,0:20:58.77,Default,,0,0,0,,“set free all those who were held in slavery
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.77,0:21:03.61,Default,,0,0,0,,all their lives by their fear of death.”
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.15,0:21:09.79,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, the apostle Paul\Npraised Jehovah for the gift of Christ Jesus.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.79,0:21:11.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And why?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.62,0:21:14.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Because he knew that all of those
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.12,0:21:17.46,Default,,0,0,0,,who would put faith\Nin the ransom sacrifice of Christ Jesus
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.46,0:21:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,would be set free.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.00,0:21:22.50,Default,,0,0,0,,But set free from what?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.50,0:21:26.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Paul says that it’s from the slavery
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.20,0:21:29.70,Default,,0,0,0,,to the “fear of death.”
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.71,0:21:32.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, why is that significant?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.54,0:21:36.51,Default,,0,0,0,,You see,\Npeople who are in fear of death
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.51,0:21:39.55,Default,,0,0,0,,are constantly afraid.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.55,0:21:43.45,Default,,0,0,0,,And, as a result,\Nthey can be manipulated and controlled.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.45,0:21:46.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, take, for example,\Nthe Nuremberg trials
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.72,0:21:49.29,Default,,0,0,0,,that occurred at the end\Nof the second world war.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.29,0:21:54.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Various Nazis who\Nhad committed horrible, terrible atrocities
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.30,0:21:56.67,Default,,0,0,0,,were brought to justice.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.67,0:21:58.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And when these individuals,\Nboth men and women,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.93,0:22:00.93,Default,,0,0,0,,were asked the simple question,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.94,0:22:05.11,Default,,0,0,0,,“How could you do these terrible things?”
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.11,0:22:07.51,Default,,0,0,0,,what did they say?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.51,0:22:09.68,Default,,0,0,0,,“We had no choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.68,0:22:11.85,Default,,0,0,0,,“If we didn’t obey,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.85,0:22:14.49,Default,,0,0,0,,they would put us to death.”
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.48,0:22:17.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Those people could be manipulated;
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.59,0:22:19.66,Default,,0,0,0,,they could be controlled;
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.65,0:22:23.49,Default,,0,0,0,,they could even get them\Nto do the most wicked things
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.49,0:22:26.19,Default,,0,0,0,,because they were afraid.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.19,0:22:29.49,Default,,0,0,0,,When we have complete confidence
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.50,0:22:32.67,Default,,0,0,0,,in our amazing God, Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.67,0:22:35.87,Default,,0,0,0,,when we have put our full confidence
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.87,0:22:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,in the ransom sacrifice\Nof his Son, Jesus Christ,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.88,0:22:43.95,Default,,0,0,0,,we can do\Nwhat the apostle Paul says here
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.95,0:22:45.95,Default,,0,0,0,,in Philippians chapter 1.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.95,0:22:48.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Will you read it with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.22,0:22:53.03,Default,,0,0,0,,At Philippians 1:28,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.49,0:22:56.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Paul says:
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.49,0:23:00.83,Default,,0,0,0,,“And in no way being frightened
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.83,0:23:03.10,Default,,0,0,0,,“by your opponents.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.10,0:23:08.01,Default,,0,0,0,,“This very thing\Nis a proof of destruction for them,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.00,0:23:11.14,Default,,0,0,0,,“but of salvation for you;
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.14,0:23:15.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and this is from God.”
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.08,0:23:18.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, brothers,\Nthat confidence in Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.38,0:23:22.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and in the ransom sacrifice\Nof Christ can set us free,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.85,0:23:27.09,Default,,0,0,0,,so that we are not afraid\Nof our opponents.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.09,0:23:29.99,Default,,0,0,0,,But another thing that can help us
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.99,0:23:32.99,Default,,0,0,0,,to overcome the fear of persecution
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.99,0:23:35.93,Default,,0,0,0,,is realizing something very important,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.93,0:23:38.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and that is that Jehovah will allow
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.77,0:23:43.24,Default,,0,0,0,,our enemies to go only so far.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.24,0:23:46.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, you remember the text\Nin 1 Corinthians chapter 10.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.58,0:23:48.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, let’s read this,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.41,0:23:52.78,Default,,0,0,0,,1 Corinthians 10:13.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.62,0:23:56.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The apostle Paul says:
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.65,0:24:00.75,Default,,0,0,0,,“No temptation has come upon you\Nexcept what is common to men.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.76,0:24:03.30,Default,,0,0,0,,“But God is faithful,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.29,0:24:05.33,Default,,0,0,0,,“and he will not let you be tempted
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.33,0:24:07.40,Default,,0,0,0,,“beyond what you can bear,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.40,0:24:09.94,Default,,0,0,0,,“but along with the temptation
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.93,0:24:13.20,Default,,0,0,0,,“he will also make the way out
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.20,0:24:17.07,Default,,0,0,0,,so that you may be able to endure it.”
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.07,0:24:20.91,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s a promise from our God, Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.91,0:24:25.55,Default,,0,0,0,,He will only allow our enemies to go so far.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.98,0:24:29.18,Default,,0,0,0,,In a well-known illustration from a book
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.18,0:24:32.85,Default,,0,0,0,,that was written in the 1600’s,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.85,0:24:37.42,Default,,0,0,0,,it shows a path\Nthat leads off to the final goal,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.43,0:24:42.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and on either side of the path,\Nthere are lions.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.20,0:24:45.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The caption to the illustration says:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.23,0:24:48.53,Default,,0,0,0,,“The lions were chained,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.54,0:24:52.78,Default,,0,0,0,,but he didn’t see the chains.”
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.77,0:24:54.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, what’s the point?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.81,0:24:59.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You see,\Nwe may encounter lions along our path
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.38,0:25:03.55,Default,,0,0,0,,on our journey to the new world.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.55,0:25:06.65,Default,,0,0,0,,But what do we need to remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.66,0:25:11.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Every one of those lions is chained.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.66,0:25:14.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we must look,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.53,0:25:18.20,Default,,0,0,0,,not at the lions, brothers,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.20,0:25:20.30,Default,,0,0,0,,but at the chains.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.30,0:25:24.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And as we concentrate\Non the fact that Jehovah loves us,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.67,0:25:26.77,Default,,0,0,0,,that he loves his people,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.78,0:25:31.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and that he will never allow\NSatan or his agents to do anything
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.55,0:25:34.39,Default,,0,0,0,,that will permanently harm us,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.38,0:25:37.58,Default,,0,0,0,,our fear of our persecutors
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.59,0:25:40.39,Default,,0,0,0,,begins to dwindle away.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.39,0:25:45.33,Default,,0,0,0,,When you see the lion,\Nremember, don’t stare at the lion.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.33,0:25:47.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Stare at the chain.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.00,0:25:52.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So then, brothers,\NI come back to the question,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.10,0:25:54.84,Default,,0,0,0,,What then do we have to fear?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.84,0:25:56.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the Bible tells us.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.67,0:25:59.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s here in Psalm 111
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.94,0:26:04.45,Default,,0,0,0,,—Psalm 111:10.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.62,0:26:12.63,Default,,0,0,0,,It says: “The fear of Jehovah\Nis the beginning of wisdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.62,0:26:17.56,Default,,0,0,0,,“All those observing his orders\Nshow good insight.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.56,0:26:21.30,Default,,0,0,0,,His praise endures forever.”
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.30,0:26:23.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that’s what we do have to fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.67,0:26:26.47,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to have a wholesome fear
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.47,0:26:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,of our wonderful God, Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.64,0:26:32.84,Default,,0,0,0,,That wholesome fear of displeasing\Nthe Almighty God of the universe
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.84,0:26:35.01,Default,,0,0,0,,is our compass.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.01,0:26:37.01,Default,,0,0,0,,It shows us the way;
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.01,0:26:40.38,Default,,0,0,0,,it tells us what we need to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.38,0:26:44.25,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter how much opposition\Nmay come upon us,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.25,0:26:48.59,Default,,0,0,0,,no matter what form\Nthat opposition may take,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.59,0:26:52.66,Default,,0,0,0,,if we are God-fearing men and women,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.66,0:26:56.10,Default,,0,0,0,,we will know exactly what we need to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.10,0:26:57.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you agree?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.77,0:27:06.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, brothers, this is not theory.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.17,0:27:08.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Our brothers and sisters around the world
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.28,0:27:12.99,Default,,0,0,0,,are living examples of the truths\Nthat we have just discussed.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.98,0:27:15.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Please watch the following video
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.68,0:27:18.18,Default,,0,0,0,,that contains heartfelt comments
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.19,0:27:22.06,Default,,0,0,0,,from persecuted brothers\Nand sisters in Russia,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.06,0:27:27.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and see why we have\Nno reason to fear persecution.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.23,0:27:35.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I was horrified when several masked officers\Nbroke down two doors
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.34,0:27:38.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and burst into the home\Nwhere the meeting was being held.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.77,0:27:41.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything happened at once
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.01,0:27:44.45,Default,,0,0,0,,—loud sounds, noise, the order:
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.45,0:27:46.49,Default,,0,0,0,,“Everyone sit on the floor!”
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.52,0:27:54.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I was overcome with fear\Nwhen they put me in handcuffs,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.52,0:27:57.29,Default,,0,0,0,,placed me in the police van,\Nand took me to jail.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.29,0:28:00.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I was afraid because I didn’t know
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.16,0:28:03.66,Default,,0,0,0,,how long I would be there\Nand what was awaiting me.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.80,0:28:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,When I was being interrogated,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.80,0:28:10.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I was afraid that I might be unfaithful\Nto Jehovah and let my brothers down.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.01,0:28:16.55,Default,,0,0,0,,After being detained, I was mostly afraid\Nabout what I would face in prison
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.54,0:28:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,—whom I would encounter, how to act,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.28,0:28:22.12,Default,,0,0,0,,how others would treat me—the unknown.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.62,0:28:33.53,Default,,0,0,0,,When one of the officers began\Nto describe how bad life is behind bars,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.53,0:28:36.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I imagined that behind\Nthe officer stood an angel
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.23,0:28:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,just like the one who\Nsupported Daniel in the illustration.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.50,0:28:43.04,Default,,0,0,0,,This helped me to calm down\Nand not to panic or be afraid.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.04,0:28:45.54,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s how Jehovah supported me.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.58,0:28:51.75,Default,,0,0,0,,At the first court appearance,\Nwhen I was brought out,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.75,0:28:55.05,Default,,0,0,0,,the brothers’ feelings impelled them\Nto show support somehow,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.05,0:28:56.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and they began applauding.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.68,0:29:00.22,Default,,0,0,0,,How that encouraged me\Nthat they were with me!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.29,0:29:04.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Fervent and sincere prayers to Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.69,0:29:06.69,Default,,0,0,0,,helped me to cope with these fears.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.16,0:29:11.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Isaiah 30:15 gave me much support.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.27,0:29:13.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I realized that tranquility and trust
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.70,0:29:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,in Jehovah are now the most important things.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.40,0:29:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Understanding this made things\Nmuch easier for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.78,0:29:25.55,Default,,0,0,0,,We took the elevator down\Nto the first floor, the doors opened,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.55,0:29:29.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and there stood a large crowd\Nof our brothers and sisters
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.75,0:29:31.75,Default,,0,0,0,,—and they all began clapping.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.09,0:29:36.76,Default,,0,0,0,,When I saw that, my emotions just welled up,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.76,0:29:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and I got a lump in my throat.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.36,0:29:42.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I felt as if I had wings;
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.36,0:29:45.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I felt the “great cloud of witnesses.”
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.84,0:29:51.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I prayed to Jehovah\Nfor calmness, courage, and wisdom
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.77,0:29:55.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and that he help me\Nnot to bring reproach on his holy name.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.38,0:29:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Almost immediately, “the peace of God”
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.48,0:30:01.28,Default,,0,0,0,,came over me, and I was calm.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.28,0:30:04.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The unpleasant sensations did not go away,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.22,0:30:06.82,Default,,0,0,0,,but I was no longer afraid.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.76,0:30:14.77,Default,,0,0,0,,While overcoming our fear, my wife and I\Ntried to go out in service every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.76,0:30:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,When you don’t concentrate on yourself
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.00,0:30:20.70,Default,,0,0,0,,but focus on helping others, fear disappears.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.07,0:30:24.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Something that helped me\Nto cope with my fears
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.54,0:30:27.38,Default,,0,0,0,,is hope,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.38,0:30:30.68,Default,,0,0,0,,looking at the situation\Nthrough Jehovah’s eyes,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.68,0:30:33.35,Default,,0,0,0,,seeing what will happen next,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.35,0:30:36.19,Default,,0,0,0,,that this is not the end of the situation,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.18,0:30:39.48,Default,,0,0,0,,but only a difficult phase\Nthrough which you can pass.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.52,0:30:45.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I was helped to cope\Nwith my fear by the words of the song:
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.19,0:30:47.19,Default,,0,0,0,,“Take one day at a time;
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.20,0:30:49.80,Default,,0,0,0,,“leave tomorrow until tomorrow;
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.80,0:30:51.97,Default,,0,0,0,,peace is what I find.”
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.97,0:30:56.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I understood that it was important\Nto solve problems as they came up 
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.50,0:30:59.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and not to be troubled\Nby what might never happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.87,0:31:02.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Fear is interesting;
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.58,0:31:05.88,Default,,0,0,0,,that is, in principle, fear can be 
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.88,0:31:10.02,Default,,0,0,0,,inside a person, and if someone\Nis afraid, that is not shameful.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.02,0:31:12.02,Default,,0,0,0,,But the question is,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.02,0:31:13.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you overcome this fear?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.59,0:31:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you get the fear under your control?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.96,0:31:19.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you overcome this surge of negativity?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.43,0:31:24.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And when my heart persuaded me to get scared,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.33,0:31:26.77,Default,,0,0,0,,then I started to pray.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.77,0:31:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I prayed to Jehovah to give me courage
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.84,0:31:33.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and not be afraid of anyone or anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.47,0:31:35.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I still say to myself,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.48,0:31:39.79,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Feliks, do not fear anybody\Nor anything except Jehovah!’
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.55,0:31:46.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Dear brothers and sisters,\NI really appreciate your support.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.55,0:31:49.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m very happy for all your letters,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.52,0:31:52.16,Default,,0,0,0,,for all your thoughts, for all your prayers.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.16,0:31:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I really appreciate it a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.40,0:31:56.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I try to do my best,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.53,0:31:59.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and I try to serve Jehovah\Nin the best way that I can.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.67,0:32:01.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I will do that forever!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.81,0:32:43.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Brothers and sisters,\Nwe know that persecution
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.14,0:32:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,is coming to us too.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.08,0:32:48.65,Default,,0,0,0,,May we trust in Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.65,0:32:52.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and overcome any fear\Nthat we have of our opposers.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.89,0:32:57.90,Default,,0,0,0,,May we be confident\Nthat any lions on our path are chained.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.89,0:33:02.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at the chains, not the lions.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.80,0:33:07.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And may we be ever guided\Nby our wholesome fear of Jehovah God.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.80,0:33:11.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you determined to fear nothing
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.11,0:33:14.28,Default,,0,0,0,,except our wonderful God, Jehovah?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.88,0:33:23.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I ask you,\NWhat do we have to fear?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.76,0:33:32.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for answering\Nthis question about fear so eloquently.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.23,0:33:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we are looking forward to the discussion
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.80,0:33:40.60,Default,,0,0,0,,by Brother Jackson on the interesting theme
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.60,0:33:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,“Are You Completely Sober?”
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.44,0:33:47.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess so, looking at the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.65,0:33:54.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you completely sober?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.05,0:33:57.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I know what you’re thinking: ‘Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.29,0:33:59.36,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Seriously?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.35,0:34:01.35,Default,,0,0,0,,‘The answer is obvious, isn’t it?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.36,0:34:03.53,Default,,0,0,0,,‘We’ve been in this Assembly Hall for hours,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.52,0:34:05.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and there’s no opportunity to drink.’
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.20,0:34:11.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So the answer to the question\Nseems rather obvious, doesn’t it?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.67,0:34:15.74,Default,,0,0,0,,But before you dismiss\Nthis question completely,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.74,0:34:19.88,Default,,0,0,0,,could there be\Nsome other meaning to this question,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.87,0:34:21.87,Default,,0,0,0,,a spiritual meaning?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.88,0:34:24.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The answer, of course, is yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.81,0:34:27.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Because when we look at the Greek text
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.32,0:34:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,upon which the Christian Greek Scriptures
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.92,0:34:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,were translated from,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.92,0:34:36.26,Default,,0,0,0,,we notice that literally\Nthe term “to be sober”
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.26,0:34:39.33,Default,,0,0,0,,occurs a number of times.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.33,0:34:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And yet, the Christian Greek Scriptures\Nof the {\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}New World Translation
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.00,0:34:45.97,Default,,0,0,0,,do not actually use the words “to be sober.”
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.97,0:34:47.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s take an example.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.97,0:34:49.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Please turn with me, if you will,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.97,0:34:54.81,Default,,0,0,0,,to 1 Peter 1:13.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.61,0:34:58.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, if you have a device,\Nyou can also quickly look
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.28,0:35:00.32,Default,,0,0,0,,at the {\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}Kingdom Interlinear{\r}{\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif} 
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.31,0:35:02.68,Default,,0,0,0,,if you wish to verify this.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.68,0:35:05.65,Default,,0,0,0,,But 1 Peter 1:13
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.65,0:35:08.59,Default,,0,0,0,,(and just the beginning of this verse),
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.59,0:35:11.89,Default,,0,0,0,,it says:\N“So brace up your minds for activity;
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.89,0:35:15.09,Default,,0,0,0,,keep your senses completely.”
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.20,0:35:19.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The Greek expression here could be translated
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.77,0:35:23.51,Default,,0,0,0,,as “being sober perfectly.”
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.50,0:35:26.47,Default,,0,0,0,,But notice that we have\Nthe expression translated
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.47,0:35:30.21,Default,,0,0,0,,as “keep your senses completely.”
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.21,0:35:33.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So that raises the interesting question,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.48,0:35:37.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Why didn’t\Nthe New World Bible Translation Committee
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.52,0:35:39.96,Default,,0,0,0,,say “to be sober”
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.95,0:35:42.62,Default,,0,0,0,,or “to be completely sober”?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.62,0:35:44.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the answer to that question
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.86,0:35:48.70,Default,,0,0,0,,goes back to your initial reaction\Nwhen you heard the title of this talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.70,0:35:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s be honest, when you heard\N“Are You Completely Sober?”
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.40,0:35:54.94,Default,,0,0,0,,what did you think of immediately?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.94,0:35:57.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Drinking alcohol or avoiding it.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.87,0:36:00.21,Default,,0,0,0,,But the majority of times
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.21,0:36:03.31,Default,,0,0,0,,that this expression\Noccurs in the Christian Greek Scriptures,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.31,0:36:07.98,Default,,0,0,0,,it does not specifically refer\Nto avoiding alcohol
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.98,0:36:11.28,Default,,0,0,0,,or becoming intoxicated with alcohol.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.29,0:36:16.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Rather, it has a larger figurative meaning.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.29,0:36:21.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So for us to follow\Nthe admonition “to be sober,”
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.30,0:36:25.40,Default,,0,0,0,,we need to know, really,\Nwhat the Bible means by that expression.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.40,0:36:27.50,Default,,0,0,0,,What is included in that?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.50,0:36:29.87,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what we’re going to briefly do
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.87,0:36:32.44,Default,,0,0,0,,is look at four different ways
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.44,0:36:34.64,Default,,0,0,0,,that the {\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}New World Translation
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.64,0:36:38.78,Default,,0,0,0,,has covered this expression.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.78,0:36:41.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And by looking\Nat the different ways in English
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.58,0:36:43.58,Default,,0,0,0,,that this has been translated,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.58,0:36:46.25,Default,,0,0,0,,we’ll see what really is involved
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.25,0:36:49.22,Default,,0,0,0,,with this expression “to be sober.”
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.22,0:36:50.49,Default,,0,0,0,,So let’s start.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.49,0:36:54.86,Default,,0,0,0,,If you turn with me, please,\Nto 1 Timothy chapter 3—
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.90,0:36:57.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And immediately we remember
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.90,0:36:59.94,Default,,0,0,0,,that 1 Timothy chapter 3
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.93,0:37:01.97,Default,,0,0,0,,is talking about the qualifications
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.97,0:37:04.37,Default,,0,0,0,,for overseers, and also it mentions
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.37,0:37:06.41,Default,,0,0,0,,what sisters should do.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.41,0:37:08.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, in verse 2 and verse 11
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.68,0:37:11.65,Default,,0,0,0,,(we won’t read it but glancing at it),
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.65,0:37:13.65,Default,,0,0,0,,in Greek,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.65,0:37:17.25,Default,,0,0,0,,the word “to be sober” literally is there,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.25,0:37:19.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and you can see it\Nin the {\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}Kingdom Interlinear.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.85,0:37:21.22,Default,,0,0,0,,But how is it translated?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.22,0:37:23.39,Default,,0,0,0,,We don’t see the word “sober,” do we?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.39,0:37:25.39,Default,,0,0,0,,The expression there is
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.39,0:37:28.43,Default,,0,0,0,,to be “moderate in habits.”
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.43,0:37:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, why did the brothers
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.00,0:37:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,translate it this way?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.60,0:37:34.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Because although it could refer
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.07,0:37:37.44,Default,,0,0,0,,to avoiding being intoxicated,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.44,0:37:41.51,Default,,0,0,0,,it has this wider meaning\Nof having good sense
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.51,0:37:44.81,Default,,0,0,0,,when it comes to things\Nlike conduct and speech
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.81,0:37:48.25,Default,,0,0,0,,or the choice of entertainment or recreation.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.25,0:37:51.85,Default,,0,0,0,,It means not going to foolish extremes
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.85,0:37:54.52,Default,,0,0,0,,or being erratic in our thinking
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.52,0:37:57.02,Default,,0,0,0,,or unbalanced in our opinions.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.02,0:38:01.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So all of that is involved\Nin this figurative meaning
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.46,0:38:04.56,Default,,0,0,0,,of the expression\Nto be “moderate in habits.”
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.57,0:38:07.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s take an example\Nby looking at another verse
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.84,0:38:12.08,Default,,0,0,0,,in the Bible as to what is involved\Nin not being extreme.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.07,0:38:16.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s turn to 1 Corinthians this time
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.01,0:38:20.82,Default,,0,0,0,,—1 Corinthians 7:31.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.65,0:38:24.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, this doesn’t use\Nthe term in Greek “to be sober,”
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.65,0:38:26.92,Default,,0,0,0,,but it gives us further information
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.92,0:38:30.79,Default,,0,0,0,,as to what’s involved\Nwith being moderate in habits.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.79,0:38:33.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So verse 31 says:
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.09,0:38:35.16,Default,,0,0,0,,“Those making use of the world
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.16,0:38:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,as those not using it to the full.”
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.33,0:38:42.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, what does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.47,0:38:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, maybe we could use\Nthis illustration to highlight it.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.07,0:38:49.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Imagine a hungry person
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.01,0:38:51.75,Default,,0,0,0,,who wants to pick fruit from a tree.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.75,0:38:54.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, a person who’s not unbalanced
Dialogue: 0,0:38:54.78,0:38:57.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and doesn’t go to extremes perhaps would be
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.35,0:38:59.35,Default,,0,0,0,,happy just to get enough fruit
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.35,0:39:01.39,Default,,0,0,0,,to satisfy his hunger
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.39,0:39:04.99,Default,,0,0,0,,or maybe to get a few extra pieces of fruit
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.99,0:39:06.99,Default,,0,0,0,,so that he could take some home.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.99,0:39:11.53,Default,,0,0,0,,But a person who was to ‘use it to the full’
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.53,0:39:13.53,Default,,0,0,0,,is that type of person
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.53,0:39:15.97,Default,,0,0,0,,who after they’ve collected everything
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.97,0:39:18.87,Default,,0,0,0,,they can get (more than they could ever use),
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.87,0:39:22.14,Default,,0,0,0,,they see the one piece\Nof fruit right up at the top
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.14,0:39:24.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and they have to have it,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.28,0:39:27.98,Default,,0,0,0,,even if it involves a certain risk.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.98,0:39:30.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So when the apostle Paul
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.22,0:39:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,said under inspiration
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.72,0:39:35.96,Default,,0,0,0,,that we\N‘shouldn’t use the world to the full,’
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.96,0:39:38.76,Default,,0,0,0,,symbolically,\Nwe could say, it’s just like this
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.76,0:39:43.03,Default,,0,0,0,,—not trying to get\N{\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}everything {\r} out of this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.03,0:39:45.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, what sort of symbolic fruit
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.57,0:39:47.57,Default,,0,0,0,,might we be tempted with?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.57,0:39:50.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, there are so many opportunities today
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.34,0:39:53.48,Default,,0,0,0,,for education, recreation, entertainment,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.47,0:39:57.77,Default,,0,0,0,,travel, vacations, employment, and business.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.78,0:40:02.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Are we truly sober\Nwhen it comes to those things,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.25,0:40:07.16,Default,,0,0,0,,or are we like the person\Nwho is trying to grab every opportunity
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.15,0:40:09.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and use the world to the full?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.89,0:40:14.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, let’s look at a second example\Nof this Greek word being used
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.90,0:40:19.91,Default,,0,0,0,,—1 Peter 4:7.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:19.90,0:40:23.30,Default,,0,0,0,,First Peter 4:7 says:
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.30,0:40:26.27,Default,,0,0,0,,“But the end of all things\Nhas drawn close.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.27,0:40:28.71,Default,,0,0,0,,“Therefore, be sound in mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.71,0:40:30.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and be vigilant.”
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.74,0:40:32.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, notice the footnote says,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.75,0:40:35.69,Default,,0,0,0,,“Or ‘alert; awake.’”
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.68,0:40:38.02,Default,,0,0,0,,But if you look at the {\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}Kingdom Interlinear,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.02,0:40:41.12,Default,,0,0,0,,it says: “Be you sober.”
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.12,0:40:43.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So in this case,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.16,0:40:45.16,Default,,0,0,0,,the brothers translated
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.16,0:40:47.30,Default,,0,0,0,,the literal term in Greek, “sober,”
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.29,0:40:50.89,Default,,0,0,0,,to be “vigilant,” or “alert” and “awake.”
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.90,0:40:52.90,Default,,0,0,0,,With regard to what?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.90,0:40:54.90,Default,,0,0,0,,With regard to our prayers.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.90,0:40:58.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s interesting that the apostle Peter\Nwas inspired to say these words.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.84,0:41:00.94,Default,,0,0,0,,No doubt he remembered the time
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.94,0:41:03.34,Default,,0,0,0,,when he wasn’t \N‘vigilant with regard to prayers,’
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.34,0:41:06.74,Default,,0,0,0,,when Jesus said “keep praying” constantly
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.75,0:41:08.75,Default,,0,0,0,,in the garden of Gethsemane.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.75,0:41:11.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And, of course,\NPeter would have remembered what resulted
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.82,0:41:16.12,Default,,0,0,0,,because of that lack\Nof being sober in a spiritual sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.12,0:41:18.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what about us?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:18.13,0:41:21.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Are we vigilant with regard to prayers?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.53,0:41:24.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Do we pray to Jehovah constantly,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.20,0:41:27.24,Default,,0,0,0,,whenever we have an opportunity\Nright through the day?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:27.23,0:41:30.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Or do we only just pray\Nwhen we wake up in the morning,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.74,0:41:34.24,Default,,0,0,0,,when we eat,\Nand before we go to bed at night?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.24,0:41:38.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, for us\Nto ‘be vigilant with regard to prayers,’
Dialogue: 0,0:41:38.15,0:41:41.45,Default,,0,0,0,,if we constantly have Jehovah in our minds,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.45,0:41:43.55,Default,,0,0,0,,then we can truly say that we are,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.55,0:41:46.82,Default,,0,0,0,,in a symbolic sense, sober.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.82,0:41:48.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, a third example
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.86,0:41:51.70,Default,,0,0,0,,—1 Corinthians chapter 15.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.56,0:41:53.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.89,0:41:55.53,Default,,0,0,0,,all of us remember very clearly
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.53,0:41:59.43,Default,,0,0,0,,the words in verse 33 about bad associations,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.43,0:42:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,but this verse is verse 34
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.40,0:42:04.44,Default,,0,0,0,,in the same context.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.44,0:42:05.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And how does it start?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.81,0:42:09.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It says: “Come to your senses
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.04,0:42:11.08,Default,,0,0,0,,in a righteous way.”
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.08,0:42:13.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Again, if we look at the literal rendering
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.41,0:42:14.78,Default,,0,0,0,,of the Greek, it says:
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.78,0:42:17.48,Default,,0,0,0,,“Sober you up.”
Dialogue: 0,0:42:17.48,0:42:20.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, what is this talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.19,0:42:22.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the study note of our Bible
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.56,0:42:26.46,Default,,0,0,0,,(and of course, you can only get this\Nin the electronic form at the moment),
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.46,0:42:29.30,Default,,0,0,0,,it says: “Come to your senses:
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.30,0:42:31.54,Default,,0,0,0,,“Paul here uses a Greek word
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.53,0:42:34.17,Default,,0,0,0,,“that literally means ‘to sober up.’
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.17,0:42:36.74,Default,,0,0,0,,“Because some of the Corinthian Christians
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.74,0:42:39.38,Default,,0,0,0,,“gave ear to apostate teachings,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.37,0:42:42.11,Default,,0,0,0,,“such as the denial of the resurrection,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.11,0:42:45.51,Default,,0,0,0,,“they were in a spiritual stupor of sorts,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:45.51,0:42:49.05,Default,,0,0,0,,“confused and disoriented as if drunk.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.05,0:42:51.65,Default,,0,0,0,,“Paul thus urges them to wake up,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.65,0:42:53.79,Default,,0,0,0,,“to shake off their confusion
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.79,0:42:57.86,Default,,0,0,0,,“by getting a clear understanding\Nof the teaching of the resurrection.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.86,0:43:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,“They needed to do so before their stupor
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.96,0:43:05.57,Default,,0,0,0,,led them to spiritual sickness\Nand even death.”
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.57,0:43:09.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So do we see why the brothers\Ntranslated it this way?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.47,0:43:12.57,Default,,0,0,0,,“Come to your senses” is not just talking
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.57,0:43:14.74,Default,,0,0,0,,about drinking wine or beer,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.74,0:43:19.61,Default,,0,0,0,,but it’s talking\Nabout avoiding bad associates
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.61,0:43:22.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and those who give wrong ideas.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:22.52,0:43:27.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So could it be that we may be affected\Nby the opinions of some,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.09,0:43:29.09,Default,,0,0,0,,maybe even within the congregation,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:29.09,0:43:32.36,Default,,0,0,0,,who say,\N“Is the end really so close?”
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.36,0:43:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,or “Is what the world offers\Nreally that bad?”
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.80,0:43:40.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Or if we were to be tempted to believe
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.20,0:43:43.70,Default,,0,0,0,,every account or report on the Internet
Dialogue: 0,0:43:43.70,0:43:46.94,Default,,0,0,0,,with regard to those taking\Nthe lead in the organization,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.94,0:43:49.71,Default,,0,0,0,,do we just quickly believe those things?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.71,0:43:52.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Or worse still, do we search the Internet
Dialogue: 0,0:43:52.81,0:43:57.78,Default,,0,0,0,,looking for juicy stories\Nabout other Jehovah’s Witnesses?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:57.79,0:44:01.09,Default,,0,0,0,,We need to remember\Nthat Satan is “the father of the lie.”
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.09,0:44:03.09,Default,,0,0,0,,He’s an expert at lying,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.09,0:44:07.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and he makes sure there are\Nplenty of lies for us to come across.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.29,0:44:10.59,Default,,0,0,0,,But if we are sober spiritually,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:10.60,0:44:13.77,Default,,0,0,0,,this means we won’t get fooled
Dialogue: 0,0:44:13.77,0:44:16.41,Default,,0,0,0,,or tricked by false stories.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.40,0:44:19.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the fourth and final example
Dialogue: 0,0:44:19.24,0:44:23.11,Default,,0,0,0,,we want to share with you\Nis in 1 Thessalonians
Dialogue: 0,0:44:23.11,0:44:27.55,Default,,0,0,0,,—1 Thessalonians 5:6.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:27.55,0:44:29.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And here again in the Greek text,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:29.55,0:44:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,we see the word “sober,”
Dialogue: 0,0:44:31.59,0:44:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,if it’s literally translated into English.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:34.96,0:44:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Verse 6 says: “So, then,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:36.99,0:44:39.46,Default,,0,0,0,,“let us not sleep on as the rest do,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.46,0:44:41.50,Default,,0,0,0,,“but let us stay awake
Dialogue: 0,0:44:41.50,0:44:43.50,Default,,0,0,0,,“and [notice, this is the expression]
Dialogue: 0,0:44:43.50,0:44:46.27,Default,,0,0,0,,keep our senses.”
Dialogue: 0,0:44:46.27,0:44:49.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what is the context of this verse?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:49.80,0:44:52.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s talking\Nabout ‘Jehovah’s day coming as a thief.’
Dialogue: 0,0:44:52.74,0:44:56.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s talking about those saying\N“Peace and security!”
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.84,0:44:59.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So in this sense,\Nto “be sober” means
Dialogue: 0,0:44:59.25,0:45:01.29,Default,,0,0,0,,we know the time we’re living in.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:01.28,0:45:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re not only spiritually awake,\Nbut we’re alert.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.49,0:45:06.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Think of this illustration:
Dialogue: 0,0:45:06.49,0:45:08.49,Default,,0,0,0,,There could be a guard,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:08.49,0:45:11.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and that guard is totally awake,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:11.23,0:45:13.27,Default,,0,0,0,,but he’s watching
Dialogue: 0,0:45:13.26,0:45:15.40,Default,,0,0,0,,the tournament on the television
Dialogue: 0,0:45:15.40,0:45:19.10,Default,,0,0,0,,—maybe it’s football,\Nsomething he’s excited about.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:19.10,0:45:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,He’s not alert to the dangers
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.44,0:45:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,that are lurking.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:23.44,0:45:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So in a similar way,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:25.44,0:45:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,we need to be totally awake spiritually
Dialogue: 0,0:45:28.48,0:45:30.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and alert to what is happening
Dialogue: 0,0:45:30.84,0:45:33.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and to the dangers that present themselves,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:33.58,0:45:36.75,Default,,0,0,0,,such as getting involved\Nwith the political issues
Dialogue: 0,0:45:36.75,0:45:39.05,Default,,0,0,0,,that we see in the world today.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:39.05,0:45:41.79,Default,,0,0,0,,To do so would make us part of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:41.79,0:45:45.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, we have to focus on God’s Kingdom
Dialogue: 0,0:45:45.26,0:45:47.53,Default,,0,0,0,,as the only true solution.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:47.53,0:45:50.90,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s what it means to be sober.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:50.90,0:45:55.91,Default,,0,0,0,,So we’ve seen\Nthose four aspects of this literal word
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.90,0:45:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,when it’s translated\Ninto English as “being sober.”
Dialogue: 0,0:45:59.44,0:46:01.64,Default,,0,0,0,,But why is that so important?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.64,0:46:03.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Brothers and sisters,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:03.64,0:46:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,as it’s been already presented\Non this program,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:06.65,0:46:11.22,Default,,0,0,0,,we know challenging times\Nare in front of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:11.22,0:46:15.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, we need to be completely sober
Dialogue: 0,0:46:15.19,0:46:18.03,Default,,0,0,0,,when we face those challenges.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:18.03,0:46:20.67,Default,,0,0,0,,This year is a special year;
Dialogue: 0,0:46:20.66,0:46:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,it marks 100 years
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.96,0:46:27.20,Default,,0,0,0,,since the appointment\Nof “the faithful and discreet slave.”
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.20,0:46:30.54,Default,,0,0,0,,That slave, when we look back\Nover the 100 years,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.54,0:46:34.28,Default,,0,0,0,,has remained awake, spiritually speaking,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:34.27,0:46:38.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and alert and has kept on reminding us\Nof the need to do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.91,0:46:40.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, it’s true.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.05,0:46:41.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Some might say: “Well, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:41.42,0:46:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,“But at times,\Nwe look back over 100 years,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.92,0:46:47.29,Default,,0,0,0,,“and there were times they got\Nexcited about a certain year or time,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:47.29,0:46:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and the end didn’t come at that time.”
Dialogue: 0,0:46:49.76,0:46:53.03,Default,,0,0,0,,But just imagine if you had a watchdog
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.03,0:46:56.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and that dog barks\Nin the middle of the night
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.20,0:46:58.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and you get up and there’s nothing there,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:58.20,0:47:00.20,Default,,0,0,0,,do you shoot the dog?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:02.27,0:47:04.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It only proves that the dog
Dialogue: 0,0:47:04.44,0:47:07.61,Default,,0,0,0,,is doing what you want it to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:07.61,0:47:11.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So in a similar way,\Nrealize the faithful slave,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:11.31,0:47:15.38,Default,,0,0,0,,yes, in their enthusiasm,\Nsometimes we have said things
Dialogue: 0,0:47:15.38,0:47:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,that maybe disappointed others.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:18.15,0:47:21.82,Default,,0,0,0,,But remember,\Nthe role of “the faithful and discreet slave”
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.82,0:47:26.16,Default,,0,0,0,,is to feed us and to keep us\Nawake spiritually and keep us alert.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:26.16,0:47:30.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And thinking about it,\Nwhen that day comes
Dialogue: 0,0:47:30.16,0:47:35.17,Default,,0,0,0,,when Jesus brings destruction\Non this wicked system of things,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:35.17,0:47:37.27,Default,,0,0,0,,where do you want to be?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:37.27,0:47:39.94,Default,,0,0,0,,on a beach drinking a martini?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:41.24,0:47:46.28,Default,,0,0,0,,climbing a symbolic tree\Nto get the last bit of fruit from this world?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:46.28,0:47:48.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Or do you want to be\Nbusy in Jehovah’s service,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:48.95,0:47:52.55,Default,,0,0,0,,whether it’s building and preaching\Nand all the things we need to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:52.55,0:47:54.05,Default,,0,0,0,,We know the answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:54.05,0:47:59.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, but to do that,\Nwe have to remain sober spiritually.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:59.03,0:48:03.37,Default,,0,0,0,,And one final point,\Nif we look in the {\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}Insight {\r} volume
Dialogue: 0,0:48:03.36,0:48:05.40,Default,,0,0,0,,under the heading “Soberness,”
Dialogue: 0,0:48:05.40,0:48:07.74,Default,,0,0,0,,there’s a very interesting point,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:07.73,0:48:10.50,Default,,0,0,0,,because Peter and Paul
Dialogue: 0,0:48:10.50,0:48:13.57,Default,,0,0,0,,used this expression in Greek.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:13.57,0:48:16.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And the {\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}Insight {\r} volume\Nmakes this very interesting comment.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:16.94,0:48:20.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It says: “In keeping his senses,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:20.21,0:48:22.81,Default,,0,0,0,,“Timothy was to realize that Paul
Dialogue: 0,0:48:22.82,0:48:25.59,Default,,0,0,0,,would not be on the scene much longer.”
Dialogue: 0,0:48:25.59,0:48:27.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Then it says about Peter:
Dialogue: 0,0:48:27.62,0:48:31.29,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Peter likewise knew\Nthat he and his fellow apostles
Dialogue: 0,0:48:31.29,0:48:33.56,Default,,0,0,0,,would not be on hand much longer.’
Dialogue: 0,0:48:33.56,0:48:35.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Then it goes on to say:
Dialogue: 0,0:48:35.56,0:48:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“Knowing the seriousness of the times,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:38.00,0:48:40.77,Default,,0,0,0,,“with growing persecution from the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:40.77,0:48:45.01,Default,,0,0,0,,“they should be \Nsound in mind, watchful, vigilant,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:45.01,0:48:47.61,Default,,0,0,0,,“and should not neglect serious prayer,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:47.61,0:48:52.18,Default,,0,0,0,,to obtain the strength\Nthey would need for endurance.”
Dialogue: 0,0:48:52.18,0:48:55.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, the faithful slave has been serving us
Dialogue: 0,0:48:55.48,0:48:58.42,Default,,0,0,0,,with spiritual food for 100 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:58.42,0:49:00.59,Default,,0,0,0,,But, friends, remember,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:00.59,0:49:04.19,Default,,0,0,0,,the faithful slave will not always be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:04.19,0:49:07.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Soon will come the time\Nwhen the remaining ones of the anointed
Dialogue: 0,0:49:07.93,0:49:10.87,Default,,0,0,0,,will be taken to have their reward.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:10.86,0:49:14.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course,\NJehovah will continue to care for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:14.23,0:49:17.83,Default,,0,0,0,,He always has a provision\Nin place to care for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:17.84,0:49:19.84,Default,,0,0,0,,But what is the important thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:19.84,0:49:23.71,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it that the faithful slave\Nwants to convey to us?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:23.71,0:49:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Just the same as Paul and Peter
Dialogue: 0,0:49:26.88,0:49:29.75,Default,,0,0,0,,wanted to convey\Nto those to whom they wrote,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:29.75,0:49:34.35,Default,,0,0,0,,we want to convey to you\Nthe importance of each one of us
Dialogue: 0,0:49:34.35,0:49:36.45,Default,,0,0,0,,being moderate in habits,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:36.46,0:49:38.73,Default,,0,0,0,,vigilant with regard to prayers,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:38.73,0:49:42.53,Default,,0,0,0,,keeping our senses,\Nnot being distracted by false stories,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:42.53,0:49:45.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and being alert to the time\Nin which we’re living.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:45.80,0:49:48.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So we leave you with that question,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.17,0:49:50.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you sober?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:50.20,0:49:52.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you {\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}completely {\r} sober?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:01.28,0:50:05.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we certainly appreciate\Nthis sobering talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:05.85,0:50:09.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You will now be interested\Nto hear what Brother Kenneth Cook
Dialogue: 0,0:50:09.69,0:50:12.59,Default,,0,0,0,,has to say on the topic
Dialogue: 0,0:50:12.59,0:50:14.83,Default,,0,0,0,,“Will You Care for It?”
Dialogue: 0,0:50:14.83,0:50:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Cook, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:17.00,0:50:21.07,Default,,0,0,0,,We care for the things\Nthat are important to us, don’t we?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:21.07,0:50:24.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And there are many of such things.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:24.07,0:50:26.97,Default,,0,0,0,,For example,\Nwe care for our families,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:26.97,0:50:31.61,Default,,0,0,0,,we care for our friends,\Nwe care for our ministry,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:31.61,0:50:35.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and above all,\Nwe care for our worship of Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:35.95,0:50:40.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And we do this faithfully to the very end.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:40.25,0:50:44.39,Default,,0,0,0,,When others need us,\Nwe’re there for them, as we’ve seen today.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:44.39,0:50:48.06,Default,,0,0,0,,During times\Nof natural disasters, civil unrest,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:48.06,0:50:53.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and severe opposition to our work,\Nwe are there for one another.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:53.07,0:50:57.61,Default,,0,0,0,,In addition to all of that,\Nour love must also, though,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:57.60,0:51:00.54,Default,,0,0,0,,be great enough to care for those
Dialogue: 0,0:51:00.54,0:51:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,whom we try to reach in our public ministry.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:03.98,0:51:08.82,Default,,0,0,0,,In this, Jesus set the example for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:08.82,0:51:12.32,Default,,0,0,0,,We can feel\Nhis caring attitude in what he said
Dialogue: 0,0:51:12.32,0:51:17.33,Default,,0,0,0,,at Matthew 9:36-38.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:17.32,0:51:22.33,Default,,0,0,0,,So please follow along at Matthew 9:36.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:23.30,0:51:25.77,Default,,0,0,0,,It says:\N“On seeing the crowds,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:25.77,0:51:28.21,Default,,0,0,0,,“he felt pity for them,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:28.20,0:51:30.60,Default,,0,0,0,,“because they were\Nskinned and thrown about
Dialogue: 0,0:51:30.60,0:51:33.24,Default,,0,0,0,,“like sheep without a shepherd.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:33.24,0:51:35.88,Default,,0,0,0,,“Then he said to his disciples:
Dialogue: 0,0:51:35.88,0:51:40.22,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Yes, the harvest is great,\Nbut the workers are few.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:40.21,0:51:42.91,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Therefore, beg the Master of the harvest
Dialogue: 0,0:51:42.92,0:51:46.56,Default,,0,0,0,,to send out workers into his harvest.’”
Dialogue: 0,0:51:46.55,0:51:50.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus felt pity for the people, didn’t he?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:50.56,0:51:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What does pity mean in this case?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:53.99,0:51:58.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The pity mentioned here\Nstems from heartfelt love.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:58.93,0:52:02.13,Default,,0,0,0,,He loved the people.\NWe love people.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:02.14,0:52:04.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s a tender feeling toward persons
Dialogue: 0,0:52:04.97,0:52:08.37,Default,,0,0,0,,in a state of need or suffering.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:08.38,0:52:10.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Like Jesus, our love for others
Dialogue: 0,0:52:10.91,0:52:15.68,Default,,0,0,0,,must include genuine care for them\N—even pity for them—
Dialogue: 0,0:52:15.68,0:52:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,so that we’re moved to help them,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:18.15,0:52:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,hoping that they respond to God’s Word
Dialogue: 0,0:52:21.52,0:52:25.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and will desire to do Jehovah’s will.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:25.13,0:52:28.37,Default,,0,0,0,,And we must do this\Nbecause caring for others
Dialogue: 0,0:52:28.36,0:52:32.73,Default,,0,0,0,,is an important part\Nof following the Christ, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:32.73,0:52:36.43,Default,,0,0,0,,In a few minutes,\Nwe will look at how we can remain focused
Dialogue: 0,0:52:36.44,0:52:40.28,Default,,0,0,0,,on compassionately carrying out our ministry
Dialogue: 0,0:52:40.27,0:52:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and helping people\Nto dedicate their lives to God.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:44.44,0:52:49.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And this will include revealing\Nwhat our yeartext is for 2020.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:49.42,0:52:52.99,Default,,0,0,0,,So as Brother Lett said earlier,\N“Stay tuned.”
Dialogue: 0,0:52:52.99,0:52:54.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Before we get to that, though,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:54.99,0:52:58.23,Default,,0,0,0,,we’ll draw out\Nsome Bible principles from long ago
Dialogue: 0,0:52:58.23,0:53:02.03,Default,,0,0,0,,that will help us today\Nin caring for the people
Dialogue: 0,0:53:02.03,0:53:06.44,Default,,0,0,0,,that we must yet reach\Nin this important ministry, or work.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:06.43,0:53:08.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Since ancient times,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:08.74,0:53:13.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah has taught his people\Nhow to care for others.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:13.61,0:53:16.71,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, the Israelites\Nwere told to show consideration
Dialogue: 0,0:53:16.71,0:53:20.45,Default,,0,0,0,,even for the animals under their care.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:20.45,0:53:23.85,Default,,0,0,0,,For instance,\Nwhen they were about to leave Egypt,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:23.85,0:53:26.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah gave them this command
Dialogue: 0,0:53:26.22,0:53:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,at Exodus 12:5, 6.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:29.92,0:53:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Please follow along.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:31.93,0:53:35.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, here is the setting:
Dialogue: 0,0:53:35.43,0:53:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah gives instructions\Nabout selecting the Passover sacrifice.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:40.43,0:53:43.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Verse 3 tells us that the Israelites
Dialogue: 0,0:53:43.17,0:53:47.34,Default,,0,0,0,,were to select the sheep\Non the tenth of the month.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:47.34,0:53:51.61,Default,,0,0,0,,With this in mind,\Nnotice what verse 5 states:
Dialogue: 0,0:53:51.61,0:53:55.61,Default,,0,0,0,,“Your sheep should be\Na sound, one-year-old male.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:55.62,0:53:59.32,Default,,0,0,0,,“You may choose\Nfrom the young rams or from the goats.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:59.32,0:54:02.26,Default,,0,0,0,,“You must care for it
Dialogue: 0,0:54:02.26,0:54:05.03,Default,,0,0,0,,“until the 14th day of this month,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:05.03,0:54:08.50,Default,,0,0,0,,“and the whole congregation\Nof the assembly of Israel
Dialogue: 0,0:54:08.50,0:54:11.40,Default,,0,0,0,,must slaughter it at twilight.”
Dialogue: 0,0:54:11.40,0:54:14.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Why was it important for them
Dialogue: 0,0:54:14.97,0:54:17.14,Default,,0,0,0,,to not only select the sheep
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.14,0:54:21.01,Default,,0,0,0,,but to “care for it until the 14th”?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:21.01,0:54:24.68,Default,,0,0,0,,To answer that question,\Nlet’s draw out two principles
Dialogue: 0,0:54:24.68,0:54:27.08,Default,,0,0,0,,that we will then apply to our ministry
Dialogue: 0,0:54:27.08,0:54:29.08,Default,,0,0,0,,—and they do apply.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:29.08,0:54:32.92,Default,,0,0,0,,First, we know that the sacrificial sheep
Dialogue: 0,0:54:32.92,0:54:36.26,Default,,0,0,0,,needed to remain unblemished
Dialogue: 0,0:54:36.26,0:54:39.53,Default,,0,0,0,,to be acceptable to Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:39.53,0:54:44.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Verse 5 said: “Your sheep should be\Na sound, one-year-old male.”
Dialogue: 0,0:54:44.53,0:54:47.73,Default,,0,0,0,,If an Israelite selected a sound sheep
Dialogue: 0,0:54:47.73,0:54:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,but then neglected it\Nand the sheep was injured in some way,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:52.01,0:54:54.25,Default,,0,0,0,,that sheep would no longer be
Dialogue: 0,0:54:54.24,0:54:57.41,Default,,0,0,0,,acceptable to Jehovah for sacrifice.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:57.41,0:54:59.41,Default,,0,0,0,,The principle:
Dialogue: 0,0:54:59.41,0:55:03.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep the sacrifice acceptable.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:03.15,0:55:07.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t neglect it\Njust because the end is close,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:07.42,0:55:12.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and we can apply\Nthat principle to our ministry.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:12.16,0:55:14.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, principle number two:
Dialogue: 0,0:55:14.59,0:55:18.06,Default,,0,0,0,,We can also be certain\Nthat a measure of compassion
Dialogue: 0,0:55:18.06,0:55:21.43,Default,,0,0,0,,was involved in what Jehovah told them there.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:21.43,0:55:26.44,Default,,0,0,0,,In this case,\Nthe sacrificial sheep was no less important
Dialogue: 0,0:55:26.44,0:55:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,just because its time,\Nso to speak, was short.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:30.88,0:55:34.08,Default,,0,0,0,,See, as we’ll see in this discussion,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:34.08,0:55:37.08,Default,,0,0,0,,this too can apply to our ministry.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:37.08,0:55:40.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And we’re wise to remember these principles.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:40.59,0:55:44.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Fittingly, it is Jehovah\Nwho sets the example for us
Dialogue: 0,0:55:44.72,0:55:46.72,Default,,0,0,0,,in showing compassion
Dialogue: 0,0:55:46.73,0:55:51.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and caring for what is important\Nto the very end.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:51.73,0:55:56.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Foremost in this\Nis how Jehovah cared for Jesus
Dialogue: 0,0:55:56.04,0:55:59.34,Default,,0,0,0,,right up to the end of his earthly ministry.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:59.34,0:56:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,For instance,\NJehovah showed his support for Jesus
Dialogue: 0,0:56:03.44,0:56:05.94,Default,,0,0,0,,by answering Jesus’ prayers.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:05.95,0:56:08.45,Default,,0,0,0,,At one point, Jesus even said:
Dialogue: 0,0:56:08.45,0:56:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,“Father, I thank you that you have heard me.”
Dialogue: 0,0:56:13.35,0:56:17.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, Jehovah voiced his support for Jesus.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:17.86,0:56:22.13,Default,,0,0,0,,At his baptism,\NJesus heard Jehovah speak from heaven,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:22.13,0:56:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,stating:\N“This is my Son, the beloved,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:26.00,0:56:28.94,Default,,0,0,0,,whom I have approved.”
Dialogue: 0,0:56:28.94,0:56:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Imagine how that encouraged him!
Dialogue: 0,0:56:31.84,0:56:34.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And then later, as Jesus was in agony
Dialogue: 0,0:56:34.91,0:56:37.48,Default,,0,0,0,,during the hours before his death,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:37.48,0:56:40.55,Default,,0,0,0,,an angel of God comforted Jesus,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:40.55,0:56:45.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and no doubt that angel\Nwas a friend whom Jesus knew well.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:45.55,0:56:49.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, from the beginning to the very end,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:49.79,0:56:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah cared for Jesus,\Nthe sacrificial “Lamb of God.”
Dialogue: 0,0:56:54.79,0:56:58.76,Default,,0,0,0,,We benefit when we apply such principles
Dialogue: 0,0:56:58.77,0:57:02.44,Default,,0,0,0,,to what we have been given to do today.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:02.44,0:57:06.54,Default,,0,0,0,,For instance, the time is short, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:06.54,0:57:11.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet, our public ministry\Nis no less important now
Dialogue: 0,0:57:11.31,0:57:14.45,Default,,0,0,0,,just because the end is close.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:14.45,0:57:16.62,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, it’s even more important
Dialogue: 0,0:57:16.62,0:57:19.46,Default,,0,0,0,,that we continue caring for this ministry
Dialogue: 0,0:57:19.45,0:57:21.69,Default,,0,0,0,,as the end approaches.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:21.69,0:57:25.89,Default,,0,0,0,,We must care for this “sacrifice of praise”
Dialogue: 0,0:57:25.89,0:57:28.76,Default,,0,0,0,,to our heavenly Father right up to the end
Dialogue: 0,0:57:28.76,0:57:32.83,Default,,0,0,0,,—that is, right up to the time\Nwhen Jehovah makes it clear
Dialogue: 0,0:57:32.83,0:57:37.24,Default,,0,0,0,,that this part of our service to him\Nhas come to an end.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:37.24,0:57:39.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Until that time,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:39.24,0:57:43.94,Default,,0,0,0,,what should be the focus\Nof our public ministry?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:43.94,0:57:46.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus stated what it should be
Dialogue: 0,0:57:46.21,0:57:50.41,Default,,0,0,0,,at Matthew 28:18-20,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:50.42,0:57:53.12,Default,,0,0,0,,so please go to those verses.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:53.12,0:57:57.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, starting at Matthew 28:18,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:57.49,0:57:59.53,Default,,0,0,0,,it says:
Dialogue: 0,0:58:07.53,0:58:11.40,Default,,0,0,0,,“Jesus approached\Nand spoke to them, saying:
Dialogue: 0,0:58:11.40,0:58:15.54,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘All authority has been given me\Nin heaven and on the earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:15.54,0:58:19.94,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Go, therefore, and make disciples\Nof people of all the nations,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:19.95,0:58:23.69,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘baptizing them in the name of the Father
Dialogue: 0,0:58:23.68,0:58:26.95,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘and of the Son and of the holy spirit,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:26.95,0:58:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘teaching them to observe\Nall the things I have commanded you.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:31.86,0:58:35.53,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘And look!\NI am with you all the days
Dialogue: 0,0:58:35.53,0:58:39.77,Default,,0,0,0,,until the conclusion\Nof the system of things.’”
Dialogue: 0,0:58:39.77,0:58:43.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So now,\Nwith these words of Jesus in mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:43.77,0:58:47.54,Default,,0,0,0,,what should be\Nthe focus of our public ministry?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:47.54,0:58:51.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the focus must be\Nto ‘make disciples of Christ
Dialogue: 0,0:58:51.01,0:58:53.51,Default,,0,0,0,,‘among people of all the nations,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:53.51,0:58:58.52,Default,,0,0,0,,teaching them and baptizing them,’\Nas Jesus stated.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:58.52,0:59:03.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Notice that Jesus’ statement\Nwas more than just a command.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:03.02,0:59:07.83,Default,,0,0,0,,He didn’t start off saying:\N“I command you! Go!”—right?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:07.83,0:59:09.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Rather, Jesus said:
Dialogue: 0,0:59:09.96,0:59:14.97,Default,,0,0,0,,“All authority has been given me . . .\NGo, therefore.”
Dialogue: 0,0:59:14.97,0:59:19.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus’ true disciples\Nwould see beyond the command
Dialogue: 0,0:59:19.87,0:59:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,embedded in those words\Nand go forth with conviction.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:24.24,0:59:25.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:25.58,0:59:29.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Because they would know\Nthat Jesus was empowered, authorized,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:29.95,0:59:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,to oversee this great work
Dialogue: 0,0:59:32.72,0:59:35.56,Default,,0,0,0,,that they were now commissioned to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:35.56,0:59:39.43,Default,,0,0,0,,He would be with them,\Nand he is with us today.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:39.43,0:59:42.47,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re absolutely confident of that fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:42.46,0:59:47.27,Default,,0,0,0,,In view of that,\Nhow can we help our Bible students
Dialogue: 0,0:59:47.27,0:59:52.01,Default,,0,0,0,,so that even more of them\Nbecome baptized disciples,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:52.01,0:59:54.71,Default,,0,0,0,,as Jesus there directed?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:54.71,0:59:57.85,Default,,0,0,0,,This is important to consider because,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:57.84,1:00:01.34,Default,,0,0,0,,while many get baptized each year,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:01.35,1:00:03.79,Default,,0,0,0,,our yearly baptism figures have remained
Dialogue: 0,1:00:03.78,1:00:06.38,Default,,0,0,0,,at about the same level for some time.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:06.39,1:00:08.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, are these good figures?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:08.52,1:00:10.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, they are.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:10.52,1:00:11.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Absolutely!
Dialogue: 0,1:00:11.92,1:00:15.22,Default,,0,0,0,,But what can we do\Nto help even more people
Dialogue: 0,1:00:15.23,1:00:19.73,Default,,0,0,0,,take this vital step\Nbefore the end comes?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:19.73,1:00:21.73,Default,,0,0,0,,To answer that question,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:21.73,1:00:25.50,Default,,0,0,0,,let’s briefly consider\Nfour ways to reach the heart.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:25.51,1:00:29.38,Default,,0,0,0,,There’s much that we can do,\Nbut we’ll just consider four ways here.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:29.38,1:00:33.72,Default,,0,0,0,,We do it through what we\Nemphasize about Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:33.71,1:00:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,what we teach our students about prayer,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:37.12,1:00:40.26,Default,,0,0,0,,how we help them get to meetings,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:40.25,1:00:43.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and how we help them handle problems.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:43.72,1:00:46.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s consider that first way:
Dialogue: 0,1:00:46.66,1:00:51.67,Default,,0,0,0,,We reach the heart\Nthrough what we emphasize about Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:51.66,1:00:54.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Our goal is to help our students see
Dialogue: 0,1:00:54.87,1:00:57.77,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jehovah cares for them.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:57.77,1:01:00.94,Default,,0,0,0,,He cares about them.\NHe loves them deeply.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:00.94,1:01:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,As we use our publications 
Dialogue: 0,1:01:03.28,1:01:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,(such as the {\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}Teach Us {\r} book)\Nwith our students,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:05.91,1:01:07.95,Default,,0,0,0,,we should prepare well
Dialogue: 0,1:01:07.95,1:01:11.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and highlight the Scriptural answers\Nto questions such as:
Dialogue: 0,1:01:11.72,1:01:14.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Does God care about us?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:14.35,1:01:17.32,Default,,0,0,0,,How does God feel when people suffer?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:17.32,1:01:21.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it possible to be Jehovah’s friend?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:21.83,1:01:23.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Discuss the answers,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:23.83,1:01:27.47,Default,,0,0,0,,draw out the meaning that brings us joy
Dialogue: 0,1:01:27.47,1:01:31.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and identify the principles\Nthat improve our life,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:31.10,1:01:35.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and help the student\Nto grow ever closer to Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:35.07,1:01:37.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Now the second way:
Dialogue: 0,1:01:37.18,1:01:41.99,Default,,0,0,0,,We reach the heart through what we\Nteach our students about prayer.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:41.98,1:01:45.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Show him or her how to pray properly,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:45.12,1:01:47.76,Default,,0,0,0,,with meaning and from the heart,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:47.75,1:01:51.19,Default,,0,0,0,,as we pray with them at each study session.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:51.19,1:01:53.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Explain that in our private prayers
Dialogue: 0,1:01:53.79,1:01:56.56,Default,,0,0,0,,we can really open up to Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,1:01:56.56,1:02:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and express feelings that we\Nmight not share with other humans.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:01.00,1:02:03.27,Default,,0,0,0,,We can also ask for God’s help
Dialogue: 0,1:02:03.27,1:02:07.34,Default,,0,0,0,,to love only what he loves.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:07.34,1:02:10.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Why can we do this with confidence?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:10.04,1:02:12.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Because Jehovah cares for us,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:12.15,1:02:17.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and we should make that very clear\Nas we teach our Bible students.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:17.15,1:02:20.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Next, the third way:
Dialogue: 0,1:02:20.19,1:02:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,We reach the heart through how we\Nhelp our students get to meetings.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:25.19,1:02:29.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Invite your Bible student\Nto attend meetings as soon as possible.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:29.60,1:02:31.90,Default,,0,0,0,,What a student sees at our meetings
Dialogue: 0,1:02:31.90,1:02:34.47,Default,,0,0,0,,may touch his heart\Nand help him to progress.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:34.47,1:02:37.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Very early on, show the video
Dialogue: 0,1:02:37.40,1:02:40.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}What Happens at a Kingdom Hall?{\r}{\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif} 
Dialogue: 0,1:02:40.71,1:02:45.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Then warmly invite him to attend with you;\Nappeal to him.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:45.48,1:02:48.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, offer transportation if it is needed.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:48.95,1:02:52.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I really appreciated getting a ride\Nto the first meeting that I attended,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:52.89,1:02:54.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and I still remember it.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:54.92,1:02:57.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Finally, the fourth way:
Dialogue: 0,1:02:57.09,1:03:01.33,Default,,0,0,0,,We reach the heart through how we\Nhelp our students handle problems,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:01.33,1:03:03.97,Default,,0,0,0,,including problems that may develop
Dialogue: 0,1:03:03.96,1:03:07.10,Default,,0,0,0,,if someone offends him or her.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:07.10,1:03:09.60,Default,,0,0,0,,This is all part of reaching the heart
Dialogue: 0,1:03:09.60,1:03:12.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and preparing and helping them.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:12.44,1:03:16.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Our Bible students\Nneed to experience Jehovah’s love
Dialogue: 0,1:03:16.41,1:03:19.88,Default,,0,0,0,,as they benefit\Nfrom applying Bible principles.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:19.88,1:03:22.78,Default,,0,0,0,,See, this helps them\Nto know Jehovah better.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:22.78,1:03:26.38,Default,,0,0,0,,To help them,\Nshow your students how to use tools
Dialogue: 0,1:03:26.39,1:03:29.59,Default,,0,0,0,,such as the {\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}JW Library{\r}® app,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:29.59,1:03:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,the {\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}Research Guide for Jehovah’s Witnesses, 
Dialogue: 0,1:03:33.03,1:03:35.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and jw.org®.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:36.53,1:03:41.47,Default,,0,0,0,,When our students are trained\Nto search for answers before baptism,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:41.47,1:03:44.51,Default,,0,0,0,,they will be better prepared\Nto handle problems
Dialogue: 0,1:03:44.50,1:03:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and get along with others.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:46.64,1:03:50.28,Default,,0,0,0,,When we do these things\Nfor our Bible students,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:50.28,1:03:52.58,Default,,0,0,0,,we show that we are really caring
Dialogue: 0,1:03:52.58,1:03:56.99,Default,,0,0,0,,for what Jehovah has entrusted to us.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:56.98,1:04:00.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Both Jehovah and his Son desire
Dialogue: 0,1:04:00.82,1:04:05.83,Default,,0,0,0,,that we help as many people\Nto the point of dedication and baptism
Dialogue: 0,1:04:05.83,1:04:08.20,Default,,0,0,0,,while there’s still time.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:08.19,1:04:10.23,Default,,0,0,0,,To succeed,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:10.23,1:04:14.67,Default,,0,0,0,,don’t spend time\Nconducting an unproductive study.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:14.67,1:04:19.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Rather, focus on “those who [are]\Nrightly disposed for everlasting life,”
Dialogue: 0,1:04:19.67,1:04:24.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and care for them\Nwith Jehovah’s blessing on your efforts.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:25.81,1:04:30.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So, then, with all of this in mind,\Nwhat is our yeartext for 2020?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:31.65,1:04:34.62,Default,,0,0,0,,It is taken from Matthew 28:19:
Dialogue: 0,1:04:34.62,1:04:39.56,Default,,0,0,0,,“Go, therefore, and make disciples . . . ,\Nbaptizing them.”
Dialogue: 0,1:04:47.07,1:04:51.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, for those of you who listened\Nto Alexa earlier in the program
Dialogue: 0,1:04:51.67,1:04:53.67,Default,,0,0,0,,or read your daily text for today,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:53.67,1:04:56.51,Default,,0,0,0,,you know that this is also\Nthe Scripture text for today,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:56.51,1:04:59.51,Default,,0,0,0,,October 5, 2019.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:59.51,1:05:01.51,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s just a coincidence.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:02.92,1:05:05.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t expect it next year.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:07.09,1:05:09.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, with that text in mind,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:09.82,1:05:12.76,Default,,0,0,0,,keep putting your heart into your ministry
Dialogue: 0,1:05:12.76,1:05:14.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and into helping people,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:14.86,1:05:17.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and be certain to take care of this ministry
Dialogue: 0,1:05:17.60,1:05:19.97,Default,,0,0,0,,with those principles we considered
Dialogue: 0,1:05:19.97,1:05:22.47,Default,,0,0,0,,to the very end.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:29.78,1:05:33.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much,\NBrother Cook, for your presentation.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:35.15,1:05:38.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Looking back on the program\Nthat we were able to enjoy,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:38.65,1:05:42.19,Default,,0,0,0,,we certainly felt encouraged\Nby being reminded
Dialogue: 0,1:05:42.19,1:05:45.89,Default,,0,0,0,,that we have no human leader
Dialogue: 0,1:05:45.89,1:05:48.46,Default,,0,0,0,,but that it is Jesus who is our Leader.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:48.46,1:05:52.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember what it says at Matthew 23:10:
Dialogue: 0,1:05:52.33,1:05:54.97,Default,,0,0,0,,“Neither be called leaders,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:54.97,1:05:57.67,Default,,0,0,0,,for your Leader is one, the Christ.”
Dialogue: 0,1:05:59.04,1:06:02.31,Default,,0,0,0,,We enjoyed also listening\Nto Brother Stephen Lett,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:02.31,1:06:05.05,Default,,0,0,0,,who emphasized that our relief ministry
Dialogue: 0,1:06:05.04,1:06:07.98,Default,,0,0,0,,is overseen and directed by Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:09.58,1:06:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m sure that you also\Nenjoyed the four videos.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:13.49,1:06:14.89,Default,,0,0,0,,The first one was entitled
Dialogue: 0,1:06:14.89,1:06:19.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}‘The Good Hand of Our God Is Upon Us . . .{\r}\N{\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}Let Us Get Up and Build.’ 
Dialogue: 0,1:06:20.39,1:06:22.99,Default,,0,0,0,,The next video provided a historical look
Dialogue: 0,1:06:23.00,1:06:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,at property acquisitions,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:25.43,1:06:27.77,Default,,0,0,0,,followed by another video related
Dialogue: 0,1:06:27.77,1:06:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,to the new construction project\Nthat is being planned.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:32.24,1:06:35.41,Default,,0,0,0,,The fourth video was\Nabout the new application
Dialogue: 0,1:06:35.41,1:06:37.81,Default,,0,0,0,,for processing applications,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:37.81,1:06:40.21,Default,,0,0,0,,followed by a presentation
Dialogue: 0,1:06:40.21,1:06:42.51,Default,,0,0,0,,on a new way to access
Dialogue: 0,1:06:42.52,1:06:45.56,Default,,0,0,0,,jw.org® audio files.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:46.92,1:06:49.52,Default,,0,0,0,,After that, we enjoyed\Nthe Scriptural discussion,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:49.52,1:06:51.86,Default,,0,0,0,,“An Attack Coming From the North,”
Dialogue: 0,1:06:51.86,1:06:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,presented by Brother David Splane\Nof the Governing Body.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:55.96,1:06:59.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And Brother Samuel Herd next encouraged us
Dialogue: 0,1:06:59.10,1:07:02.37,Default,,0,0,0,,to study the Bible with a {\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}Study Bible. 
Dialogue: 0,1:07:02.37,1:07:06.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And how we appreciate the {\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}Study Bible!
Dialogue: 0,1:07:06.61,1:07:09.71,Default,,0,0,0,,After singing a song together\Nand listening to greetings
Dialogue: 0,1:07:09.71,1:07:12.11,Default,,0,0,0,,from brothers in other places and countries,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:12.11,1:07:14.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Anthony Morris reminded us
Dialogue: 0,1:07:14.78,1:07:17.45,Default,,0,0,0,,that we have work to do.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:18.82,1:07:23.52,Default,,0,0,0,,As indicated in the news media,\Nthere are increasing problems in the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:23.52,1:07:25.52,Default,,0,0,0,,In certain areas, we can also see
Dialogue: 0,1:07:25.52,1:07:29.66,Default,,0,0,0,,increasing hostility against God’s people.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:29.66,1:07:32.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Mark Sanderson of the Governing Body
Dialogue: 0,1:07:32.47,1:07:35.34,Default,,0,0,0,,showed that we do not have to be fearful
Dialogue: 0,1:07:35.33,1:07:39.80,Default,,0,0,0,,because the Almighty is on our side.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:39.81,1:07:41.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Next, we heard the talk
Dialogue: 0,1:07:41.97,1:07:46.14,Default,,0,0,0,,by Brother Geoffrey Jackson,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:46.15,1:07:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,“Are You Completely Sober?”
Dialogue: 0,1:07:48.71,1:07:51.78,Default,,0,0,0,,We are if we keep our senses.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:53.72,1:07:57.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And finally, Brother Kenneth Cook
Dialogue: 0,1:07:57.09,1:07:59.59,Default,,0,0,0,,of the Governing Body raised the question
Dialogue: 0,1:07:59.59,1:08:01.89,Default,,0,0,0,,“Will You Care for It?”
Dialogue: 0,1:08:01.89,1:08:05.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Cook reviewed\Nhow Jehovah cared for Jesus,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:05.30,1:08:08.14,Default,,0,0,0,,the sacrificial Lamb of God,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:08.13,1:08:10.37,Default,,0,0,0,,until the very end of his life on earth.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:10.37,1:08:15.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Likewise, in harmony\Nwith the 2020 yeartext
Dialogue: 0,1:08:15.37,1:08:18.14,Default,,0,0,0,,that’s taken from Matthew 28:19,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:18.14,1:08:21.51,Default,,0,0,0,,he highlighted how\Nwe must care for our ministry
Dialogue: 0,1:08:21.51,1:08:26.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and our “sacrifice of praise”\Nuntil the very end.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:26.12,1:08:31.13,Default,,0,0,0,,This includes our efforts to help\N‘those who are rightly disposed’
Dialogue: 0,1:08:31.12,1:08:36.13,Default,,0,0,0,,to dedicate their life to Jehovah\Nand to get baptized.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:38.26,1:08:41.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we have had\Nan encouraging time together, haven’t we?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:49.68,1:08:54.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we enjoyed the various videos\Nand also the video presentations,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:54.38,1:08:58.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and we all benefited\Nfrom the Scriptural talks
Dialogue: 0,1:08:58.35,1:09:00.92,Default,,0,0,0,,delivered by members of the Governing Body.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:00.92,1:09:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we also appreciate the discussion
Dialogue: 0,1:09:04.16,1:09:07.13,Default,,0,0,0,,on the yeartext for the coming year:
Dialogue: 0,1:09:07.13,1:09:18.47,Default,,0,0,0,,“Go, therefore, and make disciples . . . ,\Nbaptizing them.”
